title: Ransom Flight
description: Jim and his brother Frank Warren are the most successful ranchers in the area. Jim is kidnapped and neighbor Abe Miller is killed. The Texas Rangers are called in to investigate the shooting, unaware a kidnapping has occurred. They get a false lead when Abe mumbles Jim's name on his death bed. The Rangers assume Jim is the killer and go to investigate. The Rangers interview Frank who is very aggressive. Jim's wife arrives and lets slip she has been to the bank. The Rangers now realize they are dealing with Jim's kidnapping as well. Frank explains the kidnappers warned not to involve the law. Frank tells the Rangers about the pickup point and a trap is set. When the money is dropped it is discovered the kidnappers want the money divided into capsules and attached to homing pigeons. The Rangers organize a helicopter to track the pigeons back to the kidnapper's lair. The Rangers then sneak up on the criminals but are spotted and a gunfight breaks out. The criminals are subdued and Jim is rescued unharmed.

title: Blood Trail
description: Dr JB Thomas staggers down a street after being attacked and badly injured. He Collapses mutter 'Gaullas' before dying. The Rangers think it is an open and shut case. Karl Gaullas' wife recently died in child birth and Thomas was the doctor involved. Gaullas confirms being at the doctors but only seeking treatment for his arm. Gaullas explains an unknown man was waiting who is later identified as ranch hand Tony Horner. The Rangers visit his employer at the Ford ranch to find Horner has not been seen since last evening. Ranger Person plays a hunch and rather than drive back to town, follows a disused track. His hunch proves correct when the body of Horner is found with two bullet wounds. A medical examination of Horner shows an advanced case of 'Hoof and Mouth disease'. The Rangers return to the ranch and encounter Mr. Baxter in the process of buying the property. He is told of Thomas and Horner's death and the desire of Ford to cover up an outbreak of disease. Ford makes a run for it but is quickly apprehended and arrested

title: The Shooting of Sam Bass
description: Sam Bass a notorious bank robber sends the Texas Rangers a note about activities of his former gang and their heists. The only problem is, Sam died 20 years ago in a bank robbery

title: Home in San Antone
description: New York City, two men rob an antique store killing the owner in the process. Shortly after the Texas Ranger receive reports of a couple of strangers arriving in the area care of Ned Watkins and old timer who suffers from kleptomania. The criminals settle into a farm and wait for the gang leader arrive and inspect their haul of diamonds. Ned delivering food can't resist and steals the booty. The criminals realize what happened and set off after Ned. The Texas Rangers stop the chase and interview Ned. Suspicion is further aroused by how the criminals acted when the Rangers arrived. Headquarters confirm the identity of the criminals, and their involvement in the robbery in New York. The Rangers go to arrest the men, but a trap is set for them by the criminals. After being captured and managing to escape the Rangers make another attempt at securing the hide out. This time their actions are successful and following a ferocious fist fight the criminals are arrested and the diamonds recovered

title: The Devil's Deputy
description: Jace and Clay go after a gang that kidnapped a man, who plead guilty to stealing 65,000 dollars in bank notes.

title: A Texas Million
description: Rangers Pearson and Morgan on the trail of an robber who busted out of prison, and they have Morgan's bumbling cousin along to help.

title: Trail Herd
description: A murderous cattle owner charges other cattle agents extraordinary rates to join his herd in crossing the country.

title: The Kid from Amarillo
description: Ranger Morgan goes undercover as a boxer to help Ranger Pearson find out who is smuggling silver into Mexico.
